<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#070709" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A standalone experiment with WebGL 2, modern CSS, and the browser rendering pipeline."
    />
    <title>The Browser Is a Material - Romain C.</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./material.css" />
    <script type="module" src="./material.js"></script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#experience">Skip to the experience</a>

    <div class="boot" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="boot__mark">RC<span>®</span></div>
      <div class="boot__track"><i></i></div>
      <p>Compiling matter</p>
    </div>

    <canvas id="material" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
    <div class="fallback-field" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="reticle" aria-hidden="true"><i></i><i></i></div>

    <header class="rail">
      <a
        class="rail__identity"
        href="#prologue"
        aria-label="Return to the beginning"
      >
        <span>R/C</span>
        <span>The browser<br />is a material</span>
      </a>

      <div class="rail__readout" aria-live="polite">
        <span><i class="status-dot"></i><b id="renderer-label">GPU</b></span>
        <span id="fps-label">-- FPS</span>
        <span>JUL. 2026</span>
      </div>

      <button
        class="rail__about"
        type="button"
        popovertarget="field-notes"
        aria-label="Open field notes"
      >
        <span>Field notes</span>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M10 3v14M3 10h14"></path>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </header>

    <div class="progress" aria-hidden="true"><i id="progress-bar"></i></div>
    <div
      class="sr-progress"
      role="progressbar"
      aria-label="Page progress"
      aria-valuemin="0"
      aria-valuemax="100"
      aria-valuenow="0"
    >
    </div>

    <nav class="stage-nav" aria-label="Rendering stages">
      <span class="stage-nav__title">Pipeline</span>
      <div class="stage-nav__links">
        <a href="#signal" data-index="01"><span>Signal</span></a>
        <a href="#style" data-index="02"><span>Style</span></a>
        <a href="#layout" data-index="03"><span>Layout</span></a>
        <a href="#paint" data-index="04"><span>Paint</span></a>
        <a href="#composite" data-index="05"><span>Composite</span></a>
        <a href="#photon" data-index="06"><span>Photon</span></a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <aside id="field-notes" class="field-notes" popover>
      <div class="field-notes__head">
        <p>Field notes / 07.2026</p>
        <button
          type="button"
          popovertarget="field-notes"
          popovertargetaction="hide"
        >
          Close <span aria-hidden="true">×</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="field-notes__intro">
        <span>One document.<br />Zero libraries.</span>
        <p>
          This page uses semantic HTML, modern CSS, and a WebGL 2 fragment
          shader. Newer features are optional, so the text remains readable when
          a browser does not support them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <ol class="feature-ledger">
        <li>
          <b>01</b><span>WebGL 2</span><em>Realtime signed-distance field</em>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>02</b><span>Scroll timelines</span><em
            >Compositor-linked progress</em
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>03</b><span>Container queries</span><em
            >Components own their breakpoints</em
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>04</b><span>OKLCH color</span><em>Perceptual interpolation</em>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>05</b><span>Popover + anchor</span><em
            >This native top-layer panel</em
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>06</b><span>CSS shape & squircle</span><em
            >Geometry beyond the rectangle</em
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>07</b><span>Discrete transitions</span><em
            >Entry and exit from display: none</em
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>08</b><span>Adaptive motion</span><em
            >Reduced-motion and power aware</em
          >
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="field-notes__foot">
        <span>Built by Romain C.</span>
        <a href="/posts/notes-from-a-web-gl-and-css-experiment/"
          >Read the build notes ↗</a
        >
      </div>
    </aside>

    <main id="experience">
      <section class="hero" id="prologue" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
        <div class="hero__eyebrow">
          <span>Essay / Experiment 002</span>
          <span>Scroll through it</span>
        </div>
        <h1 id="hero-title" class="hero__title">
          <span>The browser</span>
          <span>is a <i>material.</i></span>
        </h1>
        <div class="hero__thesis">
          <p>
            I built this page to explore how a browser turns a document into
            pixels. Scroll through six simplified stages while one shader
            changes with the explanation.
          </p>
          <div class="scroll-cue" aria-hidden="true">
            <span>Enter the pipeline</span><i></i>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="hero__edition">
          A rendering experiment<br />Romain C., 2026
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="interlude" aria-hidden="true">
        <span>Input</span><i></i><span>Photon</span>
      </div>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--left is-active"
        id="signal"
        data-scene="0"
        data-label="Signal"
        aria-labelledby="signal-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">01 / Signal</p>
          <h2 id="signal-title">Nothing begins<br />with a <i>pixel.</i></h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            Interaction starts with input: a pointer moves, a key is pressed, or
            data arrives. The browser turns those events into state the page can
            use.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            The state has changed. Nothing has been drawn yet.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Input</dt>
              <dd>Events / bytes / time</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Rate</dt>
              <dd>1–1000 Hz</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>State</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="chapter__instruction">
            <i></i> Move your pointer. The field remembers.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">EVENT</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--right"
        id="style"
        data-scene="1"
        data-label="Style"
        aria-labelledby="style-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">02 / Style</p>
          <h2 id="style-title">
            Rules collide.<br />The cascade <i>decides.</i>
          </h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            CSS rules can conflict. The cascade compares origin, layer, scope,
            specificity, and source order to choose the computed values for each
            element.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            The rules are resolved. The elements still have no geometry.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Input</dt>
              <dd>Selectors / declarations</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Operation</dt>
              <dd>Match + cascade</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>Computed styles</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <div class="cascade" aria-label="Cascade precedence diagram">
            <span style="--weight: 1">user agent</span>
            <span style="--weight: 2">author</span>
            <span style="--weight: 3">scope</span>
            <span style="--weight: 4">specificity</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">RULE</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--left"
        id="layout"
        data-scene="2"
        data-label="Layout"
        aria-labelledby="layout-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">03 / Layout</p>
          <h2 id="layout-title">
            Constraints discover<br />their <i>geometry.</i>
          </h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            Layout calculates the size and position of each box from the
            available space, intrinsic sizes, writing mode, grid tracks, and
            flex rules.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            The boxes have geometry. They have not been painted.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Input</dt>
              <dd>Styled element tree</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Operation</dt>
              <dd>Constraint resolution</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>Fragments + geometry</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <div
            class="layout-solver"
            aria-label="A three-column grid with 1.4, 0.7, and 1 fractional tracks"
          >
            <span><b>1.4fr</b><small>2 rows</small></span>
            <span><b>0.7fr</b><small>row 1</small></span>
            <span><b>1fr</b><small>row 1</small></span>
            <span><b>0.7fr</b><small>row 2</small></span>
            <span><b>1fr</b><small>row 2</small></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">SPACE</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--right"
        id="paint"
        data-scene="3"
        data-label="Paint"
        aria-labelledby="paint-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">04 / Paint</p>
          <h2 id="paint-title">Geometry acquires<br />a <i>skin.</i></h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            Paint turns the layout into drawing commands for text, borders,
            shadows, and gradients. Color spaces such as OKLCH and Display P3
            allow a wider range of color.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            The drawing commands are ready. The layers still need assembling.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Input</dt>
              <dd>Layout fragments</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Gamut</dt>
              <dd>OKLCH / Display P3</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>Display list</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <div class="spectrum" aria-label="Perceptual color spectrum">
            <span></span><b>OKLCH</b><em>P3</em>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">COLOR</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--left"
        id="composite"
        data-scene="4"
        data-label="Composite"
        aria-labelledby="composite-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">05 / Composite</p>
          <h2 id="composite-title">
            Flat things learn<br />how to <i>move.</i>
          </h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            Some painted content becomes GPU layers. The browser can move or
            fade those layers without repeating layout and paint each time.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            The frame is assembled. The display has not shown it yet.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Input</dt>
              <dd>Paint chunks</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Operation</dt>
              <dd>Layerize + raster</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>GPU textures</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <div class="layer-stack" aria-label="Composited layer stack">
            <i></i><i></i><i></i><i></i>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">LAYER</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="chapter chapter--right"
        id="photon"
        data-scene="5"
        data-label="Photon"
        aria-labelledby="photon-title"
      >
        <div class="chapter__body">
          <p class="chapter__index">06 / Photon</p>
          <h2 id="photon-title">The model ends.<br />Light <i>begins.</i></h2>
          <p class="chapter__lede">
            The browser combines the layers and sends the frame to the display.
            At 60 Hz, it has about 16.67 milliseconds before the next refresh.
          </p>
          <p class="chapter__handoff">
            One frame appears, then the process continues.
          </p>
          <dl class="chapter__facts">
            <div>
              <dt>Budget at 60 Hz</dt>
              <dd>16.67 ms</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Typical display</dt>
              <dd>8.3 million pixels</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Output</dt>
              <dd>Perception</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <button class="pulse-button" id="pulse-button" type="button">
            <span>Emit one frame</span><i aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <p class="chapter__ghost" aria-hidden="true">LIGHT</p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="manifesto"
        id="epilogue"
        aria-labelledby="manifesto-title"
      >
        <p class="manifesto__kicker">End of the experiment</p>
        <h2 id="manifesto-title">
          <span>The result is</span>
          <span>a sequence</span>
          <span>of frames.</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="manifesto__grid">
          <p>
            The browser parsed the document, resolved its styles, laid out the
            boxes, and produced paint commands. It repeated the work that
            changed, then sent another frame to the display.
          </p>
          <blockquote>
            A page is not one image.<br />It is a document being rendered.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="manifesto__credits">
          <span>Small browser experiment<br /><b>Romain C.</b></span>
          <span>Rendered locally<br /><b id="render-resolution">-</b></span>
          <span>Source<br /><b>HTML / CSS / JavaScript</b></span>
        </div>
        <a class="restart" href="#prologue"><span>Run it again</span><i>↑</i></a
        >
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      <p>Romain C. / Experimental web edition / 2026</p>
      <p>A small study of how browsers turn documents into pixels.</p>
    </footer>

    <noscript>
      <div class="noscript">
        JavaScript is required for the live material. The essay remains
        readable.
      </div>
    </noscript>
  </body>
</html>
